import{_ as e,a as t,d as n,h as r,i,l as a,m as o,o as s,v as c}from"./index-DIZDA0gI.js";var l={class:`lp-page`},u={__name:`PrivacyView`,setup(u){return(u,d)=>(c(),o(a,null,[e(s),n(`div`,l,[e(t),d[0]||=r(`<main><section class="lp-container lp-pagehero" style="text-align:left;"><h1 style="font-size:clamp(36px,5vw,64px);margin-left:0;">Privacy Policy</h1><p style="margin:0;text-align:left;">How SmartDisc collects, uses, and protects your data.</p></section><section class="lp-section lp-section--tight"><div class="lp-container"><div class="lp-prose"><span class="lp-prose__meta">Last updated: 1 June 2026</span><h2>1. Who we are</h2><p> SmartDisc GmbH, Stresemannstraße 374, 22761 Hamburg, Germany (&quot;SmartDisc&quot;, &quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;) operates the website at smartdisc.io and the SmartDisc mobile app for iOS and Android. We are the controller of your personal data as defined under the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). </p><p> Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:privacy@smartdisc.io">privacy@smartdisc.io</a></p><h2>2. What data we collect</h2><h3>Website visitors</h3><p> We collect only the data your browser sends as part of standard HTTP requests: IP address, browser and OS type, referring page, and pages viewed. This data is stored in server logs for up to 14 days for security purposes and then deleted. We use no third-party analytics, no advertising pixels, and no cookies beyond those strictly necessary for the site to function. </p><h3>Pre-order customers</h3><p>When you place a pre-order we collect:</p><ul><li>Name and email address</li><li>Shipping address</li><li>Payment method details (processed by our payment provider — we never see your full card number)</li><li>Order and correspondence history</li></ul><h3>App users</h3><p> The SmartDisc app stores throw data (distance, speed, spin, timestamp) locally on your device. If you enable optional cloud backup in Settings, an encrypted copy is stored on servers in Frankfurt (EU users) or Virginia (US users). We have no access to the content of your throw data. The only data transmitted to our servers without your active opt-in is crash reports, which contain no throw data and are deleted after 30 days. </p><h2>3. How we use your data</h2><ul><li><strong>Order fulfilment</strong> — to process and ship your pre-order</li><li><strong>Customer support</strong> — to respond to questions and warranty claims</li><li><strong>Legal obligations</strong> — invoicing, tax records as required by German law</li><li><strong>Security</strong> — server log data to detect and investigate abuse</li></ul><p> We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or automated decision-making. We do not sell or share your data with third parties for their own commercial purposes. </p><h2>4. Legal basis for processing</h2><p> We process pre-order and shipping data on the basis of <strong>contract performance</strong> (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR). We process server log data on the basis of our <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in securing our infrastructure (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). Where you have opted into cloud backup, processing is based on your <strong>consent</strong> (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR), which you can withdraw at any time in app Settings. </p><h2>5. Data retention</h2><p> Order and invoicing records are retained for 10 years as required by German commercial law (§ 257 HGB). Email correspondence is retained for 3 years after the last exchange. Server logs are deleted after 14 days. You may request earlier deletion of personal data where it is no longer required for the above purposes. </p><h2>6. Your rights</h2><p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p><ul><li>Access a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li><li>Correct inaccurate data</li><li>Request deletion where data is no longer necessary</li><li>Object to processing based on legitimate interest</li><li>Data portability in a machine-readable format</li><li>Lodge a complaint with the Hamburg data protection authority (HmbBfDI)</li></ul><p> To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@smartdisc.io">privacy@smartdisc.io</a>. We will respond within 30 days. </p><h2>7. Cookies</h2><p> This website sets no advertising or tracking cookies. A single session cookie is used to maintain your pre-order login state and expires when you close your browser. No consent banner is required for this cookie under the ePrivacy Directive. </p><h2>8. Third-party services</h2><p> We use a payment processor (Stripe, Inc.) to handle card transactions. Stripe&#39;s privacy policy applies to data you enter on the payment form. We use a transactional email provider (Postmark) to send order confirmations; your name and email address are shared with them for this purpose only and are not used for marketing. Both providers are bound by data processing agreements in line with GDPR requirements. </p><h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2><p> If we make material changes to how we handle your data, we will send an email to active pre-order customers and update the &quot;Last updated&quot; date above. Continued use of the site or app after changes take effect constitutes acceptance. </p></div></div></section></main>`,1),e(i)])],64))}};export{u as default};